divs: Sighting DetailsWas in my home and saw out my window two flashes in the sky. Beautiful bright orange in color and over the lake. May have been asteroids...you tell me. Saw two in the western sky over Lake Opechee in Laconia, New Hampshire at exactly 5:00 PM EST. By the time I got my SLR 6 megapixel camera one had vanished. Took twelve successive shots from my porch through an open window till the second one vanished. I was very excited to have seen two and photographed one.

Summary: Saw two streams of orange fire decending. Got camera and one vanished. Took 12 secessive photos.
